Lea here with design feedback and proactive CSS/frontend guidance for Step 10 (Someday/Maybe).

## Design Feedback

1. **Domain type**: +1 for simple struct. No state machine needed -- items are either on the list or activated (moved to inbox). This is simpler than WaitingForItem which had Active/Resolved states.

2. **Activate action**: Activate-to-inbox only for Step 10. The user story says "moves to inbox for re-clarification" as the primary flow. Activate-to-next-actions adds context selection complexity and can be deferred.

3. **Driver**: +1 for Luca continuing. This is a straightforward CRUD page, same pattern as Waiting For.

## Proactive CSS/Frontend Guidance

Someday/Maybe is the simplest list page -- no metadata badges (no waiting_on, no context), no date display needed in the list items. Just title + actions (activate, edit, delete).

### HTML Structure

```html
<div class="someday-maybe">
    <h1>Someday / Maybe</h1>

    <!-- Add form: single field -->
    <form method="post" action="/someday-maybe" class="someday-maybe__add" ...>
        <label for="someday-title">Add idea</label>
        <div class="someday-maybe__add-row">
            <input type="text" id="someday-title" name="title"
                   placeholder="Something you might want to do someday..."
                   maxlength="300" autocomplete="off"
                   class="someday-maybe__add-input">
            <button type="submit" class="someday-maybe__add-submit">Add</button>
        </div>
    </form>

    <!-- Empty state (from US-GTD-6) -->
    <div class="someday-maybe__empty-state">
        <p>No ideas parked yet. When something's interesting but not actionable right now, put it here. You'll review this list weekly.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Item list -->
    <ul class="someday-maybe__list" role="list" id="someday-maybe-list">
        {% for item in items %}
        {% include "someday_maybe_item.html" %}
        {% endfor %}
    </ul>
</div>
```

### Each Item

```html
<li class="someday-maybe-item" id="someday-maybe-{{ item.id }}">
    <span class="someday-maybe-item__title">{{ item.title }}</span>
    <a href="..." class="someday-maybe-item__edit" aria-label="Edit: {{ item.title }}">Edit</a>
    <form ...>
        <button type="submit" class="someday-maybe-item__activate-button"
                aria-label="Activate: {{ item.title }}">Activate</button>
    </form>
    <form ...>
        <button type="submit" class="someday-maybe-item__delete-button"
                aria-label="Delete: {{ item.title }}">Delete</button>
    </form>
</li>
```

### CSS

This is the simplest list component -- follows the exact same pattern as projects. Single-field add form (like projects), simple item rows (title + action buttons).

```css
/* ---- Someday/Maybe ---- */
.someday-maybe {
    padding-block-start: var(--space-lg);
}

.someday-maybe h1 {
    margin-block-end: var(--space-lg);
}

.someday-maybe__error {
    background-color: var(--color-danger-light);
    color: var(--color-danger);
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-md);
}

/* Add form -- single field, matches projects__add */
.someday-maybe__add {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: end;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-lg);
}

.someday-maybe__add label {
    inline-size: 100%;
    margin-block-end: var(--space-xs);
}

.someday-maybe__add-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    inline-size: 100%;
}

.someday-maybe__add-input {
    flex: 1;
    min-inline-size: 10rem;
}

.someday-maybe__add-submit {
    flex-shrink: 0;
}

/* Item list */
.someday-maybe__list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
}

.someday-maybe-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    padding-block: var(--space-sm);
    padding-inline: var(--space-sm);
    border-block-end: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}

.someday-maybe-item:first-child {
    border-block-start: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}

.someday-maybe-item__title {
    flex: 1;
    min-inline-size: 0;
    overflow-wrap: break-word;
}

/* Action buttons -- muted text-button pattern */
.someday-maybe-item__edit {
    color: var(--color-fg-muted);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    text-decoration: none;
    flex-shrink: 0;
}

.someday-maybe-item__edit:hover {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
}

.someday-maybe-item__activate-button {
    background: none;
    border: none;
    padding: var(--space-xs);
    cursor: pointer;
    color: var(--color-fg-muted);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
}

.someday-maybe-item__activate-button:hover {
    background: none;
    color: var(--color-primary);
}

.someday-maybe-item__delete-button {
    background: none;
    border: none;
    padding: var(--space-xs);
    cursor: pointer;
    color: var(--color-fg-muted);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
}

.someday-maybe-item__delete-button:hover {
    background: none;
    color: var(--color-danger);
}

/* Edit form */
.someday-maybe-item__edit-form {
    flex: 1;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    min-inline-size: 0;
}

.someday-maybe-item__edit-input {
    flex: 1;
    min-inline-size: 0;
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-sm);
}

.someday-maybe-item__edit-save {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-sm);
    border: none;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    cursor: pointer;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    background-color: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
}

.someday-maybe-item__edit-cancel {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    color: var(--color-fg-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    flex-shrink: 0;
}

.someday-maybe-item__edit-cancel:hover {
    color: var(--color-fg);
    text-decoration: underline;
}

/* Empty state */
.someday-maybe__empty-state {
    color: var(--color-fg-muted);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    text-align: center;
    padding-block: var(--space-xl);
}
```

### Key Points

1. **`current_page` = `"someday_maybe"`** for the GTD nav highlighting
2. **Empty state text from US-GTD-6**: "No ideas parked yet. When something's interesting but not actionable right now, put it here. You'll review this list weekly."
3. **"Activate" button label** -- this is the GTD term for moving something from Someday/Maybe back into the system. It should be clear that activating sends the item to the inbox.
4. **Single-field add form** -- same pattern as Projects. Simplest add form in the app.
5. **No metadata badges** -- unlike Waiting For (person badge) or Next Actions (context badge), Someday/Maybe items are just titles.

